{"/service/ndnp/au/batch_au_jacobs_ver01/data/sn84020645/00513684253/1908032201/1057.xml":{"full_text":"WATERWAYS 1\nIMPROVEMENT\nMeaning of Visit of John\nA* Fox*\nALABAMA'S SPECIAL INTEREST\nState Will Be Moat Benefited by\nImprovement.\nIrcNMtr Daw. Wrttaa *1 Paeallar\nCw4IIImi la llilMa* Which\nCM! for AM la Dn\u00abl.|a.al\nof Natural Rcaoarcaa.\n\u2022T. I. em\u00bbBVBS\u00abm DAWK.\nThe presene* In this city of Hon.\nJohn A- Fox, on an errand of publicity\nIn connection with the work of the\nNational River* and Harbor* Congress\naccentuate* sharply the relation of\nAlabama to the areat purpose of se\ncuring $50.ooo.ooo each year for water\nway development.\nMany men In many plaee* through*\nout this State feel that they have re\ncognised tho Importance of waterway\nImprovement and have worked for It\nfor years; but largely a* related to\ntheir own Congressional district*. In\nview of this narrow way of Inter\npreting the State\u2019* need* no great\nblame attache* to- our Congressmen for\nexpending their energies getting \u201cpork''\nout of the barrel each time the River*\nand Harbor* till ws* Introduced. We\nhave beautiful specimen* of' \u201cpork\u201d in\nthe dam at Wetumpka (absolutely use\nless now and forever, useless unless\nthe Coosa la opened), in the dams and\nlocks above\u2019 Tuscaloosa, constructed\nwithout relation to down-stream needs,\nand In the dribbles of appropriations\ngiven In earlier years to the Alabama\nIn order to paetfy clamor. -Under the\nmethod of appropriation prevalent un\ntil the day when groat Improvements\nbscame placed on the \"continuing con-.\ntract\" basis, and even now. the Riv\ners end ftarbors Ml!. has been a pro\nlific source of dicker end trad* be\ntween Congressmen of opposite par\nties; fer the reason that a Democrat\nIn Southern States could not pacify hts\nconstituents unless some way. some\nhow be brought a little Federal monay\nInto hts district; the arbiter of such\nmonay haa been consistently Republi\ncan- These conditions are thoroughly\nfamiliar to the leading man of all th*\nStates and will not bo further dwelt\nupon hero. They are mentioned to\nmake clear the evolution that hae gone\nforward and\u2019 called Into being the Na\ntional Rivers and Harbors Congress.\nTh* purpose of that Congress I* to\nlift river and horber Improvement at\nonce and forever out of the realm of\nparty polities, treating all Improbable\nwaterways or feasible canals as na\ntional assets to be developed by a na\ntional policy, whether in the Solid\nSouth or the Solid North.\nThe difference Is the vast distance\nthat lies between petty polities and\nstatesmanship. Under the new pur\npose the Interest of Atabams in water\nway development should be Immedi\nately Increased, for It will give eur\nState a fighting chance for rapid de\nvelopment on merit alone. A vast\nmerit lies In the water systems ef thle\nState because they lead to vast ton\nnage or vast power loomed to He In\nert so long as tsmporislng methods\nare used. Let us ask oursslvss a\nquestion Ilk* this\u2014What great use\nwill the Tomblgbee and Warrior works\nbe to tho State unless Mobile Is truly\na deep water point with a good chan\nnelt ead-we see at-once that one <tar\nveiopment has relation to another\nfor good or 111, and that therefore the\nquestion Is not to any sense one to be\nhampered by the lines of Congressional\ndistricts. The broader view Is full of\nhope for Alabama and therefore every\nman who I* interested In the develop\nment of th* State should rally to the\nsupport ef th* National. Rivera and\nHarbors Congress far more earnestly\nthen we have ever done to the nar\nrower view.\nUnder the purpose to spend *50.000,\n000 a year for ten years and thus Im\nprove In a decade every one of th*\n45,000 miles of Improvable waterways\nforth* nation. Alabama would b* care\ntally considered as to th* contribution\nto National wealth mad* by Immediate\n(very on* of ua know th* answer\u2014\nAlabama with ten billion tons of Iron\nor*, with 1.0*0 square miles of coal,\nnon for to the osa by river route than\nany other larae aeeeosibl* body in th*\neeuatry ,w|th countless tons of ce\nment, with a ereat bay and port to\nt'd In aoeorn mode tine the hurrying\nSouthward trend of exports, with a\nfront door opening on the nearing\ngoal route of th* world's trade, with\npower to be made by making naviga\nbility\u2014Alabama would receive attan\ntlon among the earliest.\nWe have \"what all the world's a\nseeking\" and the world can reach it\nonly in vaat quantities by water that\nnature has already set here ter th*\npurpose. 1\nUntil Mobil* la a deop water port\nwith a broad channel Demopolls will\nnever got its full growth, neither will\nTusealoosa. neither will th* Warrior\nCoal fields b* fully developed. Until\nth* Coosa Is developed. Montgomery\nwilt never roach Its own great devel\nopment. nor will Mobile rsndor Its full\nservice to Gadsden and Anniston and\nother eltioe over the richest Iron de\nposits of th* 8tat*. With the Coosa\nchained, thl* city will leap, with Mo\nbile channel deepened every part of\nthe State south of the Tennessee would\nreceive an Impetus that would reset\nto th* benefit of every enterprise in th*\nState; for the way out and In would\nbe easier and safer. Under th* n*w\npurpose the men of Mobil* would not\nhav* to scheme and scramble for every\nInch of depth gained on th* way to the\nGulf; but th* port's relation to the\nfreight back of It would lie considered\nand acted upon.\nMr. Fox is thus seen to be the svsn\ngel of a new gospel, whoso message Is\nsane and Important. In that message\nMontgomery has th* keenest Interest,\nboth Immediate and remote. The Im\nmediate effect can be shown to mean a\nsaving In freights of f710.02 a year on\nWestern products.handled to this point.\nMr. Fox made this clear in his speech\nat th* Commercial Club Friday night,\nbut th* Sfures will be reserved for a\nsecond communication. The remote In\nterest of the city lies in the fact that\nft* future as a great centre. South\nern metropolis #f activity, depands up\non tho latent force in the Coosa now\ndoing to wasta. but destined under the\npurpose of the Rivers and Harbors\nCongress to pour Into this city a pow\nOr to handlo and manufacture the pro\nducts of tha Coo** floated here by th*\nwater that also gave*the power.\nP\u00ab TODAY'S DURn.\nCream P\u00bb*\u00ab, SSrts. a desea.\nChocolate Eclair**, M mil a teua.\nON\u00abr aa early ea hmIUc from\nKANDY KITCHEN.\nHind* A Hyatt. Phase 03.\nCONED POE GtFFKNBERG.\nNaa Arrested la Bcaacaiar Said te Ea\nWaste4 Is Chicago.\nBirmingham. March 21\u2014(Special.)\u2014\nDetective Mike Dugan, of Chicago,\nAccompanied by a bank cashier of that\ncity, arrived hare today to gat Earl\nOtffenberg, who Is wanted in Chicago on\na charge of forgery and said to be\nwanted in several other parts of the\nUnited States on a similar charge.\nOlffcnberg was arrested at Bessemer.'\nA suburb of Birmingham, where he\nhas been clerk In the Grand Hotel, go\ning under the name of H. IB. Bradley,\nand has a large following of friends.\nThe accused denied hie identity de\nspite hie IdentlDeatlon by the men who\ncame after him. Habeas corpus pro\nceedings Vttl be heard Monday.\nGUtenberg or Bradley is an expert\npenman and It la asserted that he has\nbeen drawing pen pictures under which\nnames \"of prominont artiste were placed\nForged checks are the cause of the ar\nrest. The detective has requisition pa\npers for tho prisoner.\n\u201cspecial Easter offering.\u201d\n-Cent end. trenears tailored te taste\ntrim nU '\u2666reel BLUB SERGE guaran\nteed net te fade, shrink or eeehle, $32.\nPRICKBTT-GBRSON CO.\nMACH IK MEMPHIS.\nBabb's Men Give Athletics a Geed\nEna.\nMemphis, Tenn., March 21\u2014(Special.)\n\u2014The locals had the Philadelphia\nAmericans beaten until the sixth In\nning. when the visitors pounded Sav\ntdsca tor flve runs.\nThe weather was cold, but both\nteams employed but two pitchers each.\nChappelle held t